n use after the Norman Conquest long enough to give rise to a surname. Modern use as a given name is probably a transferred use of the surname, rather than a revival of the Old English name."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ier","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from Yiddish <i>ber</i> ‘bear’, probably influenced by the early medieval European practice of giving animal names to people. It is often paired with   Dov   in order to provide a Hebrew name in certain rituals."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gossuin or Goswin Ier DE MONS DE CHIEVRES-DE FRANCONIE was born in 1055, in Baudour, Hainaut, Belgium, his mother, Benoite DE FRANCE, was 75 and his father, Goswin de Chièvres, was 35. He had at least 3 sons and 1 daughter with Ermengarde Chaumont. He died in 1093, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1055–AFT 1093":"1055–1093","1055–1093":"1055–1093","1050–1088":"1050–1088","1030–1088":"1030–1088","1073–1167":"1073–1167","1085–1171":"1085–1171","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","0980–Female":"0980–Surnud","1020–Male":"1020–Surnud","1090":"1090","1055":"1055","1088":"1088","abt 1085":"umbes 1085","1020":"1020","1085":"1085","1030":"1030","1073":"1073","1171":"1171","1050":"1050","1093":"1093","1049":"1049","1167":"1167","0980":"0980","AFT 1093":"1093","Baudour, Hainaut, Belgium":"Baudour, Hainaut, Belgia","Morlanwelz-Mariemont, Hainault, Belgium":"Morlanwelz, Hainaut, Belgia","Mons, Hainaut, Belgique":"Mons, Hainaut, Belgia","Landkreis Stendal, Sachsen-Anhalt, Allemagne":"Landkreis Stendal, Sachsen-Anhalt, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1055–AFT 1093":"1055–1093","1055–1093":"1055–1093","1050–1088":"1050–1088","1030–1088":"1030–1088","1073–1167":"1073–1167","1085–1171":"1085–1171","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","0980–Female":"0980–Kuollut","1020–Male":"1020–Kuollut","1090":"1090","1055":"1055","1088":"1088","abt 1085":"noin 1085","1020":"1020","1085":"1085","1030":"1030","1073":"1073","1171":"1171","1050":"1050","1093